---

<section id="faq" class="faq-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <p>Everything you need to know about the robot suite</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>What frameworks power these robots?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>SEO Robot and Article Robot use CrewAI for multi-agent orchestration. Newsletter Robot uses PydanticAI for structured data validation. All robots leverage Pydantic schemas for quality control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I customize the robots for my specific needs?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes! Professional and Enterprise plans include API access and custom integrations. Enterprise customers get dedicated custom agent development tailored to their workflows.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>How does the SEO Robot ensure topical consistency?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The SEO Robot analyzes your existing content to build a topic mesh, ensuring new articles maintain topical flow and internal linking consistency. It uses NetworkX for graph-based topic modeling.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>What's the quality guarantee for generated content?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>All content passes strict Pydantic validation. Article Robot guarantees >90% uniqueness and >0.85 relevance. Newsletter Robot filters content with >0.8 relevance scores. Automated retry logic ensures quality.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>How does Newsletter Robot find relevant content?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>It uses Exa AI's neural search and content extraction APIs. Results are filtered by relevance score (>0.7 threshold), deduplicated, and validated against Pydantic schemas before curation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>What's included in "all API costs covered"?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We cover OpenAI/Anthropic LLM costs, Exa AI search credits, and Firecrawl scraping within your plan limits. No surprise bills for API usage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I deploy these robots on my own infrastructure?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Enterprise customers get white-label deployment options and dedicated infrastructure. Professional plan includes API access for custom integrations with your existing systems.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question">
          <span>How fast is content generation?</span>
          <span class="icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>SEO Robot and Article Robot generate articles in <15 minutes. Newsletter Robot curates and sends in <5 minutes. Blacksmith CI/CD provides 2x faster builds vs standard GitHub Actions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-section {
    padding: 6rem 0;
    background: var(--color-light-gray);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-dark);
  }

  .section-header p {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-gray);
  }

  .faq-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .faq-question {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-question:hover {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item.active .icon {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }

  .faq-answer {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.3s ease, padding 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item.active .faq-answer {
    max-height: 500px;
    padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .faq-answer p {
    color: var(--color-gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .section-header h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .faq-question {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const faqItems = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item');
  
  faqItems.forEach(item => {
    const question = item.querySelector('.faq-question');
    
    question?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const isActive = item.classList.contains('active');
      
      // Close all items
      faqItems.forEach(i => i.classList.remove('active'));
      
      // Open clicked item if it wasn't active
      if (!isActive) {
        item.classList.add('active');
      }
    });
  });
</script>
